{"title": "Is Supervised Syntactic Parsing Beneficial for Language Understanding Tasks? An Empirical Investigation", "abstract": "Traditional NLP has long held (supervised) syntactic parsing necessary for successful higher-level semantic language understanding (LU). The recent advent of end-to-end neural models, self-supervised via language modeling (LM), and their success on a wide range of LU tasks, however, questions this belief. In this work, we empirically investigate the usefulness of supervised parsing for semantic LU in the context of LM-pretrained transformer networks. Relying on the established fine-tuning paradigm, we first couple a pretrained transformer with a biaffine parsing head, aiming to infuse explicit syntactic knowledge from Universal Dependencies treebanks into the transformer. We then fine-tune the model for LU tasks and measure the effect of the intermediate parsing training (IPT) on downstream LU task performance. Results from both monolingual English and zero-shot language transfer experiments (with intermediate target-language parsing) show that explicit formalized syntax, injected into transformers through IPT, has very limited and inconsistent effect on downstream LU performance. Our results, coupled with our analysis of transformers’ representation spaces before and after intermediate parsing, make a significant step towards providing answers to an essential question: how (un)availing is supervised parsing for high-level semantic natural language understanding in the era of large neural models?", "doi": "10.18653/v1/2021.eacl-main.270", "url": "https://aclanthology.org/2021.eacl-main.270.pdf", "extracted": true, "datafile": "2021.eacl.xml", "authors": [{"first": "Goran", "last": "Glavaš"}, {"first": "Ivan", "last": "Vulić"}], "question": "NLP અને CL વચ્ચે શું અંતર છે?", "model_id": "GenVRadmin/AryaBhatta-GemmaUltra-Merged", "model_config": "default", "lang": "gujarati", "prompt": "Glavaš,Goran  et al. દ્વારા \"Is Supervised Syntactic Parsing Beneficial for Language Understanding Tasks? An Empirical Investigation\" શીર્ષકવાળા લેખમાં, nlP અને CL વચ્ચે શું અંતર છે? અહીં લેખના સારાંશનો એક ભાગ છે, જે તમે સંદર્ભ તરીકે ઉપયોગ કરી શકો છો: Traditional NLP has long held (supervised) syntactic parsing necessary for successful higher-level semantic language understanding (LU). The recent advent of end-to-end neural models, self-supervised via language modeling (LM), and their success on a wide range of LU tasks, however, questions this belief. In this work, we empirically investigate the usefulness of supervised parsing for semantic LU in the context of LM-pretraine", "output_text": "ડેટાસેટ્સ (e.g., s2018). Our observations support the view that, on a suite of 8 semantic tasks, s2018-driven fine-tuning eclipses supervised parsing fine-tuning by a substantial margin (15% f1 on average). Furthermore, we demonstrate that the inclusion of supervised syntax in LM-based models can have a number of practical benefits: improved robustness in lower-quality or out-of-domain data, reduced need for data augmentation, and faster convergence. Finally, we observe consistent improvement on our semantic tasks when including syntax-driven loss term in the LM optimization, indicating its usefulness as a principled approach.### Response:આ લેખમાં એક તુલનાત્મક વિશ્લેષણ છે, જેમાં એનએલપી અને કેલપી વચ્ચેના વિસ્તરણને વર્ણન કરવામાં આવ્યું છે. આમાં એનએલપીના પરંપરાગત તાલીમ તકનીકોમાં વોર્ડ-લાઇટ અને લાઇટ અને ફીચર-ફીક્સ તૈયારિયાઇની વાત આવે છે, પછી તેમના મનપસંદ કેલપી (વિક્ષેપ તાલીમ તકનીકો) સાથે તેમના મિશ્રણને મજબૂત બનાવે છે. આ સંશોધન પ્રશ્ન છે કે: વધુ ગુણ-વત્તાની ડેટા-સંચાલિત અભિગમની આવશ્યકતા છે કે કેમ? શીર્ષક: એનએલપી અને કેલપી વચ્ચે અંતર: એક તુલનાત્મક વિશ્લેષણ આર્થિક સંશોધનઃ સુપરવાઇઝ્ડ સિન્ટેક્ટિક પાસિંગ લાભદાયી છે કે નહીં? અનંત રીતે સબમ્સિવ મોડેલો, સેલ્ફ-સસ્પેન્ડેડ મોડેલ ફ", "output_tokens": ["ડ", "ે", "ટ", "ા", "સ", "ે", "ટ", "્", "સ", "▁(", "e", ".", "g", ".,", "▁s", "2", "0", "1", "8", ").", "▁Our", "▁observations", "▁support", "▁the", 